This paper is primarily focused on the problem of adversarial robustness in neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses attacks on the model, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new model for robust classification, which falls under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
